Introduction
The internet has been around since the 80s
The web has been around since the the 90s
To user the web you need:
- Web Servers, to host resources like documents
- URL that identify those resources on that web Servers
- Protocols that can be used to transfer resources (HTTP CURL)
- Web Browser, to view and use those resources

HTML
  Is the basic markup for the web
  Evolving towards more interactive elements
  elements - tags - attributes
Example of using subject with space (%20) words
  href="mailto:example@bethanyspieshop.com?subject=Interested%20in%20pies
  data- attributes are special aatributes that you can add to html tag, allows you to add custom info
    <button data-order="cherry-pie">Order</button>
CSS
  Styling mechanism for the web
CSS Selectors
  when assigning a specific child.
      .columns > div:nth-of-type(2)
Media Queries
  Design Start with mobile devices first
  meta viewport --> <meta name="viewport" content='width=device-width, initial-scale=1'/>
  create class for mobile, desktop, print and hide those that are not needed using display: none
  Syntax
    @media print {
      .mobile, .desktop {
        display: none
      }
      .print {
        display: block;
      }
    }

    @media screen and (min-width: 768px) {
      .mobile {
        display: none;
      }
      .desktop {
        display: block;
      }
    }
